# UI & Component Conventions

## Brand Palette (Hertz — 2024 Sustainability Report)

- Primary gold (PANTONE 7406 C): `#F4C300` / `var(--hertz-primary)`
- Black: `#141618` / `var(--hertz-black)`
- Chart success: `#2E7D32` / `var(--chart-success)`
- Chart info: `#5C6B7A` / `var(--chart-info)` (muted blue-gray)
- Chart accent: `#7A6B5E` / `var(--chart-accent)` (warm taupe)
- Chart secondary: `#5C7C6B` / `var(--chart-secondary)` (sage)
- Text: `#1A1A1A`
- Gray: `#666666` / `#808080` for chart neutrals
- Background: `#FFFFFF`
- Subtle gold: `var(--hertz-primary-subtle)` for highlights

## Table Styling Standard

All data tables follow this pattern:
- Header: `bg-[var(--hertz-black)]` with `text-white` column headers
- Rows: `hover:bg-[var(--neutral-50)]`, `border-b border-[var(--neutral-100)]` separators
- Limit to **5 rows** by default with a "View All" button (full-width, gray background)
- "View All" buttons span the table width, not as inline links

## Metric Tiles

- Background: `bg-[var(--hertz-black)]` (black tiles)
- Text: white for values, muted for labels
- Titles: **bold**

## Charts

- Y-axis: `Y_TICKS = [0, 25, 50, 75, 100]` assumes percentages. For count metrics, dynamically compute ticks.
- Empty state: Check `data.series.every(s => s.values.every(v => v == null))` — `weekLabels.length === 0` is never true because weeks are always generated.
- Null vs 0: `null` means "no data" (skip in chart), `0` means "measured zero." Don't conflate them.
- Separate time filters per chart section (Summary uses `selectedPresetKey`, trends uses `trendsTimePresetKey`).

## Phone Number Formatting

Only apply locale-specific formatting when the country code matches:
- `+1` → US format `(XXX) XXX-XXXX`
- All others → display raw digits
- Show country flag emoji from `flagForCode()` helper

## Slot Composition Pattern

`LeadDetail` accepts an `enrichmentSlot` prop for pluggable forms. Use the same pattern for GM views that need customizable sub-sections (e.g., directive forms, review panels).

## Context Destructuring Safety

When using `useApp()` or `useData()`, always verify that every destructured value is actually passed to children. The `selectTask is not defined` crash came from destructuring `selectLead` but forgetting `selectTask`. In JSX without TypeScript, this is a silent `undefined` that only crashes at runtime.

## Provider Order

Auth and App providers must be at the root (`main.jsx`), not nested inside conditionally-rendered components. Current hierarchy: `AppProvider → AuthProvider → App (DataProvider → AppRoot)`.
